    {
      "id": "PopularPost111429",
      "post_content": "If you want to hit [Darksteel Colossus](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Darksteel Colossus), try [Return to Dust](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Return to Dust).  \n  \nAs far as this, to hell with suicide black. [Hallow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hallow).  \n  \n@Kryptnyt:  \n  \nHallow is better used AGAINST cards such as those. Spending mana on your own Earthquake or Chain Reaction and THEN Hallowing is not advisable, as Hallow prevents all damage from a spell, and the purpose of those spells is to kill all your opponents' creatures. And using Hallow on this is not like using a card to gain 5 life, it's like using a card to gain 10 life. You have to remember, you're nullifying the self-destructive part of this spell and THEN gaining 5 life as a topper. In this deck that I have, with a full playset of Ashes to Ashes and a full playset of Hallows, I also run two CoP: Blacks. A deck full of self-damaging black things (such as [Flesh Reaver](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flesh Reaver)s, [Kezzerdrix](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kezzerdrix)es and this) is the only way I can justify using such a narrow card as CoP: Black. The ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "MacBizzle",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost111429\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">If you want to hit <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Darksteel Colossus\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Darksteel Colossus\">Darksteel Colossus</a>, try <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Return to Dust\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Return to Dust\">Return to Dust</a>.<br/><br/>As far as this, to hell with suicide black. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hallow\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hallow\">Hallow</a>.<br/><br/>@Kryptnyt:<br/><br/>Hallow is better used AGAINST cards such as those. Spending mana on your own Earthquake or Chain Reaction and THEN Hallowing is not advisable, as Hallow prevents all damage from a spell, and the purpose of those spells is to kill all your opponents' creatures. And using Hallow on this is not like using a card to gain 5 life, it's like using a card to gain 10 life. You have to remember, you're nullifying the self-destructive part of this spell and THEN gaining 5 life as a topper. In this deck that I have, with a full playset of Ashes to Ashes and a full playset of Hallows, I also run two CoP: Blacks. A deck full of self-damaging black things (such as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flesh Reaver\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flesh Reaver\">Flesh Reaver</a>s, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Kezzerdrix\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kezzerdrix\">Kezzerdrix</a>es and this) is the only way I can justify using such a narrow card as CoP: Black. The ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 111429)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '111429'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy46803\">MacBizzle</span>\r\n                                (10/7/2011 5:04:25 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": "PopularPost185060",
      "post_content": "@MacBizzle  \nIf you use hallow on this, its like using one card to gain 5 life. [Circle of Protection: Black](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Protection: Black) would be preferable, and [Hallow](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hallow) is better used with things like [Earthquake](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Earthquake) and [Chain Reaction](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chain Reaction).  \nEdit; My point was, if you were using hallow on a mass-damaging spell, you would gain enough life to force your opponent to find a different way to kill you than through damage. Using Hallow when you cast Ashes to Ashes is the same as just casting a big [Healing Salve](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Healing Salve), and it takes away from the function of the card. Ashes is good because it is a 2-for-1. Ashes+Hallow is only a sorcery speed 2-for-2 at four mana. It just doesn't get me excited.",
      "posted_by": "Kryptnyt",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost185060\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">@MacBizzle<br/>If you use hallow on this, its like using one card to gain 5 life. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Circle of Protection: Black\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Circle of Protection: Black\">Circle of Protection: Black</a> would be preferable, and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Hallow\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hallow\">Hallow</a> is better used with things like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Earthquake\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Earthquake\">Earthquake</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Chain Reaction\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chain Reaction\">Chain Reaction</a>.<br/>Edit; My point was, if you were using hallow on a mass-damaging spell, you would gain enough life to force your opponent to find a different way to kill you than through damage. Using Hallow when you cast Ashes to Ashes is the same as just casting a big <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Healing Salve\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Healing Salve\">Healing Salve</a>, and it takes away from the function of the card. Ashes is good because it is a 2-for-1. Ashes+Hallow is only a sorcery speed 2-for-2 at four mana. It just doesn't get me excited.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '185060'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy24840\">Kryptnyt</span>\r\n                                (3/2/2012 2:01:02 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
